All Classes

Class Summary
Class Description
AuberGame
AuberGame is responsible for handling multiple screens and provides some helper methods for this purpose (Game.setScreen(com.badlogic.gdx.Screen)), alongside an implementation of Game for use.
DesktopLauncher
the desktop launcher holder with the main function
GameEndScreen
GameEndScreen is an extension of ScreenAdapter to create and render the end game screen.
GameScreen
GameScreen is an extension of ScreenAdapter to create and render the game.
GridGraph
Used to calculate how the operative needs to move by following the path.
GridHeur
A Heuristic generates estimates of the cost to move from a given node to the goal.
GridNode
A representation of a node with in the map.
GridNode.Pos
A class to represent a position
GridPath
A connection between two points of the map
HealthBar
Draws a rectangular health bar with black background.
HUD
Creates and loads the heads up display.
InstructionsScreen
Instruction is an extension of ScreenAdapter to create and render the instruction screen.
MapRenderer
The map render.
NotificationWindow
Creates a scrolling notification window that can have notifications added to it in diffrent colours.
Operative
Creates an operative that goes to the systems and attacks them.
Player
The player sprite.
PlayerHealthBar
Draws the health bar of the game
Systems
Create and maneges the systems that the players and operatives use.
TeleporterDialog
Override the the Dialog to add methods for the teleports.
TitleScreen
TitleScreen is an extension of ScreenAdapter to create and render the title screen.
